---
import Layout from '@/components/layout/Layout.astro';
import { getEntry } from 'astro:content';

const warningEntry = await getEntry('core', 'bainbridge-warning');
---

<Layout
  title="The Bainbridge Warning | Oscillatory Fields"
  description="Executive field manual for identifying the gap between high AI capability and inadequate governance infrastructure."
>
  <div class="pt-32 pb-24 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-display italic text-text-primary mb-4">The Bainbridge Warning</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary">Diagnosing Institutional AI Failure and the Behavioral Layer Exposure.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex gap-4 mb-16">
      <a 
        href="/bainbridge-warning.pdf" 
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-accent text-bg-dark rounded-none font-semibold hover:bg-white transition-colors"
      >
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 10v6m0 0l-3-3m3 3l3-3m2 8H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z"></path></svg>
        Download Full PDF
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:italic prose-a:text-accent hover:prose-a:text-white">
      {warningEntry ? (
        <h2>1. Governance Theater vs. Behavioral Layer Exposure</h2>
        <p>Most organizations operate with "Governance Theater" (policy statements). We measure "Behavioral Layer Exposure" (actual operational changes).</p>
        
        <h2>2. The Warning</h2>
        <p>The Bainbridge Warning identifies the phenomenon where increased transparency masks decreased reliability or increased restrictions. It is the leading indicator of systemic governance failure.</p>
      ) : (
        <p>Content loading...</p>
      )}
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
